# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 15 (advanced): seed the supercooled melt so it refreezes.
#
# In hysteresis.lmp the cooled melt supercools all the way to 300 K without
# refreezing: a small, defect-free periodic cell offers no nucleation site.
# Here we plant one.  A small sphere of atoms at the box center is restrained
# to its lattice sites so it stays crystalline through the melt and templates
# regrowth on cooling.
#
# The restraint is built by hand so the target co-dilates with the NPT box:
#   * fix store/state stores the INITIAL FRACTIONAL coordinates (xs ys zs),
#   * three atom-style variables rebuild the target abs. position each step
#     from the current box (xlo + xs0*lx ...) and form a restoring force,
#   * fix addforce applies that force.
# Unlike fix spring/self (which tethers to fixed absolute coordinates), this
# keeps the seed at the CURRENT equilibrium lattice spacing at every
# temperature, so it never strains against the thermally expanded hot box.
#
# Result: the seeded melt DOES refreeze (unlike the unseeded run), but only
# near ~450 K -- far below Tm.  A small curved seed is sub-critical near Tm
# (Gibbs-Thomson), so it cannot freeze the melt at Tm; only the flat interface
# of the two-phase method (coexist.lmp) can.  This is why a seed cures the
# supercooling artifact but cannot, by itself, measure the melting point.

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p
lattice fcc 4.05
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 4.05 4.05 4.05
region box block 0 8 0 8 0 8
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (32.4 32.4 32.4)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 2048 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (32.4 32.4 32.4)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.001 seconds
mass 1 26.98
pair_style eam/fs
pair_coeff * * Al_mm.eam.fs Al
Reading eam/fs potential file Al_mm.eam.fs with DATE: 2007-06-11
velocity all create 300.0 12345 mom yes rot yes
timestep 0.002
thermo 5000

variable temp equal temp
variable vat  equal vol/atoms

# central spherical seed (box center = 16.2 Ang for an 8 x 4.05 box)
region sphere sphere 16.2 16.2 16.2 9.0 units box
group  seed region sphere
177 atoms in group seed

# store the seed's INITIAL FRACTIONAL coordinates once (N=0 -> never updated)
fix seed0 seed store/state 0 xs ys zs

# co-dilating target position, rebuilt from the current box each step
variable txx atom xlo+f_seed0[1]*lx
variable tyy atom ylo+f_seed0[2]*ly
variable tzz atom zlo+f_seed0[3]*lz
variable dxs atom x-v_txx
variable dys atom y-v_tyy
variable dzs atom z-v_tzz
variable drs atom sqrt(v_dxs*v_dxs+v_dys*v_dys+v_dzs*v_dzs)

# ramp the restraint on over the first 10000 steps, then hold it for the run
variable kgrow equal 10000
variable gate  equal "(step/v_kgrow)*(step<=v_kgrow)+(step>v_kgrow)"

# adaptive stiffness: gentle (k0) far from home, stiffening (k0+k1) near home
# so returning atoms lock into place; v_keff has units of force/distance
variable k0   equal 3.0
variable k1   equal 9.0
variable d0   equal 0.6
variable keff atom v_gate*(v_k0+v_k1/(1.0+(v_drs/v_d0)*(v_drs/v_d0)))

# three atom-style force components pointing at the moving target
variable fxx atom -v_keff*v_dxs
variable fyy atom -v_keff*v_dys
variable fzz atom -v_keff*v_dzs
fix pull seed addforce v_fxx v_fyy v_fzz

# diagnostics: seed deviation from its target, and the fcc-coordinated count
compute dravg seed reduce ave v_drs
compute drmax seed reduce max v_drs
compute cna all cna/atom 3.8
variable isfcc atom "c_cna==1"
compute nfcc all reduce sum v_isfcc

# equilibrate at 300 K, zero pressure
fix relax all npt temp 300.0 300.0 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 2.0
run 10000
